
"H-how long w-will she be in-in a co-coma?"
"I'm afraid I don't know Miss Xavier." I could feel my body trembling, an emptiness filling me. Nodding again, I choked out the question, the answer to which confirmed all my fears.
"Is there a chance of her recovering?" Glancing Dr Burns, I saw that he looked defeated, shoulders slumping a little as he answered.
"I wish I could say that she would, but that would be giving you false hope." The doctor took in another deep breath before continuing. "I am sorry to say that she has only a three percent chance of waking up from her coma." His voice was low, gentle and full of sympathy as he spoke the words that ripped my already broken world apart.